etomica.data.types

Class CastToDouble

  • java.lang.Object
    • etomica.data.DataProcessor
      • etomica.data.types.CastToDouble
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    DataPipe, IDataSink

    public class CastToDouble
extends DataProcessor
    A DataProcessor that converts a Data instance into a DataDouble. Copies an element of the input data to the DataDouble's encapsulated value and returns the DataDouble instance. Casting for various types of Data is performed as follows:
    • DataDoubleArray. Uses only first element of array.
    • DataDouble. Does nothing, and returns input data directly.
    • DataInteger. Performs a simple cast of the int to a double.
    • DataGroup. Uses DataExtractor to locate a DataDouble in DataGroup. Other Data in group are discarded.
    Attempts to cast other Data types will produce an IllegalArgumentException by processDataInfo.
